Example
Return the string value of different variables:
<?php
$a = "Hello";
echo strval($a) . "<br>";
$b = "1234.56789";
echo 
  strval($b) . "<br>";
$c = 
  "1234.56789Hello";
echo strval($c) . "<br>";
$d = 
  "Hello1234.56789";
echo strval($d) . "<br>";
$e = 
  1234;
echo strval($e) . "<br>";
?>

Definition and Usage
The strval() function returns the string value of a variable.
Syntax
strval(
variable
);
Parameter Values
Parameter
Description
variable
Required. Specifies the variable to check
Technical Details
Return Value:
The string value of the
variable
on success
Return Type:
String
PHP Version:
4.0+

